metadata.name: k3rnel #194
metadata.description:
Self-organizing future-jazz geometry for like-minded pixel based neighbourhoods. 


********
Glossary
********

'Self-organization' → the process by which individuals organize their communal behaviour to create global order by interactions amongst themselves rather than through external intervention or instruction.

'Future-jazz-geometry' → propulsive syncopated visual rhythms, polyphonic ensemble playing, varying degrees of improvisation, and often deliberate distortions of pitch and timbre.

'Like-minded' → sharing the same opinions, ideas, or interests. 

'Pixel' → the smallest addressable element in an all points addressable display device; so it is the smallest controllable element of a picture represented on the screen.

'Neighbourhood' → a spatial unit, in which face-to-face social interactions occur.

Touch to listen, go fullscreen

metadata.name: RGB Elementary Cellular Automaton #372
metadata.description:
Stephen Wolfram's Elementary Cellular Automaton where 3 different rules are drawn in the Red, Green and Blue color components of the image.

Rules are selected randomly among a pre-selection of 53 rules from which nice behaviors emerge.

Tokens can have a cell size in the [1; 20] range.

metadata.name: Ailerons #38
metadata.description:
Ailerons, littering the factory floor, custom made and ready to be fitted to their respective aircraft. An accent trickles across the canvas, coloring any object in its path.

A study of light, built entirely in a 2d renderer, creating light and shadow with math and logic.

Press 's' to save a .png

Created with p5.js and chroma.js

metadata.name: CHIP #166
metadata.description:
A CHIP is being constructed by using two brushes that are painting on the board through deterministic noise, and then turned squared and pixelated and blended into each other, with colours selected from 21 different colour schemes. How many iterations, and the speed and size of the added parts determines the final composition. 

You can stop the iterations by pressing S, and download the current composition by hitting D, and restart/reload the iterations by pressing R.

Notes
The thumbnail generation takes a while and the render/iterations in non-GPU browser can be quite slow. Chrome/Firefox recommended.

metadata.name: Viral Refraction #87
metadata.description:
"Viral Refraction" is a mesmerizing generative art piece that offers a unique perspective on the ongoing pandemic. 

The close-up view of different variants of the COVID-19 virus is rendered in an abstract and dynamic composition, with the use of vibrant colors and intricate shapes to create a sense of movement and depth. 

This artwork highlights the unique characteristics of variants and evokes a sense of uncertainty and unpredictability that has become synonymous with the ongoing pandemic. 

This generative piece serves not only as a visual representation of the COVID-19 variants but also as a reflection on the challenges posed by the virus and its impact on the world. It's a conversation starter that is sure to leave a lasting impression on all who view it.

Disclaimer:
The use of the variant names in this artistic project are purely for the sake of creating a visual representation of the virus. This artwork is not meant to provide any scientific or factual information about viruses and should not be used for any medical or research purposes. The artist's interpretation of the virus is solely for creative expression and is not intended to reflect actual characteristics of the virus.

metadata.description:
Title: Five Body Problems: Limhamn
Media: Interactive WebGL, resolution variable

A randomized composition of digital artifacts. Scans of limestone samples from Malmö, Sweden. A broken TV on the sidewalk in NYC. Original photography and textures. Stream of consciousness text. Lorenz attractors.

* Mouse to orbit. Scroll wheel to zoom.

metadata.name: Anarchy #216
metadata.description:
"Anarchy" aims to pay tribute to the Impressionist masters and explore the interplay between randomness and control. My goal was to capture the bold use of color and the fleeting nature of light and movement that is so characteristic of the Abstract Impressionist style. 

This piece uses a total of 12 color palettes, each one inspired by a different Impressionist painter. Some artists have two palette variations, while others only have one.

I wanted to create something that was unique and that would reflect my own visual emotions while also paying homage to the artists that inspire me. "Anarchy" is part of my exploration of the relationship between randomness and intention, and a celebration of the enduring legacy of the Impressionist masters.

Made by wandurz using p5.js 
January 2023

metadata.name: codeTurning 2: push&POPing #68
metadata.description:
The codeTurning project aims to reflect my journey from traditional tools to code, in which any day I learn a new skill.
Join me towards something new for me. Something different from the previous.
Sometimes we will stand on the shoulders of giants.
 
Let's explore and see how far we get.
 
Lesson 2: push&POPing
 
With the sole initial aim of exploring push() and pop(), this stop along the way allows us to delve into the beautiful whimsy of basic colored geometric shapes. I'm having fun.

metadata.name: Release #34
metadata.description:
[…]

More than anything she had wanted to show him where she had lived, where, at a specific time every year, endless fields sent a new cycle of pods on their way.

She preferred to experience these moments alone, imagining the spectacle was being performed just for her. The whole act carried a promise of new beginnings, of paths yet to be taken.

She wasn't really part of any of this, but she too had the coordinates to her own life programmed into her genes.

Any decision would be true now, any path free.

A chorus of explosions sounded as the field burst open.

[…]

–

You can append these parameters to the URL:

[scale=<number>] scale the renderer.
[long-side=<number>] define the number of pixels of the longest side.
[animation=false] skip animating the lines.
[mode=monotone] activate monotone mode.
[detail=<number 0–1>] coarser (0) or finer (1) lines, default: 0.5.

Press [control / command + s] or [tap and hold] to save the current frame.
	- in normal mode: PNG file.
	- in monotone mode: SVG file, suitable for plotting.

Note: The monotone SVG file has no defined dimensions. It is suitable for plotting at 30 × 30 cm. with a 0.25 mm. pen tip. When plotting in larger sizes, you can increase the [detail] parameter to keep contrast with the same pen.

metadata.description:
An exploration of a distorted petals creating a wide range of abstract and organic compositions.

&density=2 / &density=3 / &density=4

metadata.name: Shattered Moons #189
metadata.description:
🌘🌗🌖Shattered Moons🌔🌓🌒

Explore deep space moons through this pure SVG generative experiment.

Features:
- Striped Background
- Shadows
- Vapors
- Horizontal Vapors
- Meteors
- Colored Meteors
- White Moon (0.5%)

SVG being a vectorial format, this work can be displayed/printed at any size.
Press 's' on Live View to save the SVG.
Press 'p' on Live View using a Chromium based browser to export as PNG.

Also, to fully enjoy your piece, I'd suggest to use a Chromium based browser as the SVG renderer gives more details.
